{{Infobox person | name = Hans Cappelen | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date |1903|12|18|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Kviteseid]], Norway | death_date = {{Death date and age|1979|10|21|1903|12|18|df=y}} | death_place = | nationality = Norwegian | other_names = | parents = | children = | relatives = | spouse = | occupation = jurist, businessperson and resistance fighter | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = | awards = [[Order of St. Olav]] }}
'''Hans Cappelen''' (18 December 1903 &ndash; 21 October 1979 ) was a Norwegian jurist, businessperson and resistance fighter.
He was born at [[Kviteseid]] in [[Telemark]], Norway. He was a son of Supreme Court Attorney Didrik Cappelen (1873-1941) and Antoinette Therese von der Lippe (1876-1934). He was a brother of [[Didrik Cappelen (born 1900)|Didrik Cappelen]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://tore.vamraak.no/slekt/slekt.asp?indnr=14804|title =Didrik Cappelen|publisher=tore.vamraak.no|accessdate= May 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://snl.no/Cappelen|title=Cappelen|publisher= Store norske leksikon|author=Jon Gunnar Arntzen |accessdate= May 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://lokalhistoriewiki.no/index.php/Cappelen|title=Cappelen|publisher= lokalhistoriewiki.no |accessdate= May 1, 2017}}</ref>
He held a degree in law and worked in senior positions in the [[Philips|Philips Group]] and was a member of the board of Norsk AS Philips. Under the [[German occupation of Norway]] during [[World War II]], he was arrested and sent to prison. He published the memoir ''Vi ga oss ikke'' (Nasjonalforlaget, 1945) and was a Norwegian witness in the [[Nuremberg trials]] in 1946. He was decorated Knight, First Class of the [[Order of St. Olav]] in 1970.<ref name=heh-1973>{{cite encyclopedia |encyclopedia=[[Hvem er Hvem?]] |year=1973 |title=Cappelen, Hans |edition=11 |editor-first=Bjørn |editor-last=Steenstrup |location=Oslo |publisher=Aschehoug |language=Norwegian |url=http://runeberg.org/hvemerhvem/1973/0102.html |accessdate=12 June 2013 }}</ref>
