'''Shep Hyken''' is an American [[customer service]] expert, author, and speaker. His book, ''The Amazement Revolution'', was a bestseller<ref>{{cite web |title=Hardcover Advice & Misc. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2011/04/24/hardcover-advice/ |website=The New York Times |accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref>.

==Customer service==
Hyken's message is that in dealing with customers, businesses should be honest, courteous, and train their staff appropriately.<ref name=consistency>{{cite news|last1=Hyken|first1=Shep|title=Consistency Is the Key to Amazing Customer Service|url=http://www.crmbuyer.com/story/Consistency-Is-the-Key-to-Amazing-Customer-Service-79560.html|accessdate=25 July 2014|work=CRM Buyer|publisher=ECT News Network|date=5 December 2013}}</ref><ref name="Rory Vaden">{{cite news|title=Shep Hyken on The Rory Vaden Show Episode 13: "Amazing Service"|url=http://roryvaden.com/blog/the-rory-vaden-show-episode-13-amazing-service-with-shep-hyken/|accessdate=25 July 2014|work=Rory Vaden Show|agency=RoryVaden.com|publisher=Southwestern Consulting|date=27 August 2013}}</ref> He has been interviewed several times on Fox News, where he has weighed in on several customer service scandals, including complaints against [[Trump University]],<ref name="bogus college">{{cite news|title=NY AG Files $40M Lawsuit Against Donald Trump|url=http://www.foxbusiness.com/on-air/money-with-melissa-francis/index.html#http://video.foxnews.com/v/2630380054001/ny-ag-files-40m-lawsuit-against-donald-trump/?playlist_id=1671716501001|accessdate=25 July 2014|work=FoxBusiness.com|agency=Money with Melissa Francis|publisher=Fox News Network, LLC|date=26 August 2013}}</ref> the [[General Motors]] recall,<ref name=GM>{{cite news|title=Reaction to GM's CEO|url=http://video.foxnews.com/v/3419400505001/reaction-to-gms-ceo-on-capitol-hill/?playlist_id=86929#sp=show-clips|accessdate=25 July 2014|work=FoxNews.com|publisher=FOX News Network, LLC.|date=1 April 2014}}</ref> the UPS and Amazon delay in holiday shipping,<ref name="UPS late with mail">{{cite news|title=UPs, FedEx, and retailers under fire for holiday shipping delays|url=http://video.foxbusiness.com/v/2977355360001/ups-fedex-and-retailers-under-fire-for-holiday-shipping-delays/#sp=show-clips|accessdate=25 July 2014|work=FoxBusiness.com|publisher=FOX News Network, LLC.|date=26 December 2013}}</ref> and [[Comcast|Comcast's]] refusal to close accounts at customer request.<ref name="Comcast nightmare">{{cite news|last1=Halligan|first1=Shannon|title=Customer service expert: How to break up with your service provider|url=http://www.kshb.com/news/local-news/customer-service-expert-how-to-break-up-with-your-service-provider|accessdate=25 July 2014|publisher=kshb.com|date=16 July 2014}}</ref>

Hyken started Shepard Presentations in 1983.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rise of the social media architect: eight jobs you never knew existed|url=http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/rise-social-media-architect-eight-jobs-knew-existed/1396029|website=CampaignLive.co.uk|accessdate=1 May 2017}}</ref>

==Books==
Hyken is the author of several books that offer advice about retaining customers. In 1993, the Alan Press published Hyken's ''Moments of Magic''. This book leverages Hyken's more than twenty years' experience in customer service.<ref>Hyken, Shep. Moments of Magic. Amazon's digital services. 2012.</ref>

In 1999, the Alan Press published ''The Loyal Customer: A Lesson From a Cab Driver'' which narrates the secrets of a taxi driver who builds a loyal customer base.<ref>Hyken, Shep. The Loyal Customer: A Lesson From a Cab Driver. Alan PR. 1999.</ref>

In 2009, Wiley published ''The Cult of the Customer: Create an Amazing Customer Experience That Turns Satisfied Customers Into Customer Evangelists''. The book outlines a strategy for leading customers and employees through five cultural phases, from uncertainty to satisfaction.<ref>Hyken, Shep. design a strategy that leads both customers and employees through five distinct cultural phases – from "uncertainty" to "amazement." Wiley. 2009.</ref>

In 2011, Greenleaf Book Group published Hyken's ''The Amazement Revolution: Seven Customer Service Strategies to Create an Amazing Customer (and Employee) Experience''.<ref name=blogtalkradiio>{{cite news|title="The Amazement Revolution" with Shep Hyken|url=http://www.blogtalkradio.com/goalachievers/2012/02/28/the-amazement-revolution-with-shep-hyken|accessdate=25 July 2014|work=BlogTalkRadio|publisher=BlogTalkRadio.com|date=February 2012}}</ref> The Amazement Revolution was on several bestseller lists: number eleven on the ''New York Times'' list,<ref name="NYT eleventh">{{cite news|title=Best Sellers: Hardcover Advice, How-To And Miscellaneous: Sunday, April 24th 2011|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9A07E1D8153EF937A15757C0A9679D8B63|accessdate=25 July 2014|work=New York Times|publisher=New York Times Company|date=24 April 2011}}</ref> number three on the ''Wall Street Journal'' list, and number one on ''USA Today's'' list.<ref name="mentions Wall Street Journal">{{cite news|title=The Amazement Revolution: Seven Customer Service Strategies to Create an Amazing Customer (and Employee) Experience|url=http://www.abebooks.com/Amazement-Revolution-Seven-Customer-Service-Strategies/10518118850/bd|accessdate=25 July 2014|work=AbeBooks.com|publisher=Amazon.com}}</ref>

In 2013, Greenleaf Book Group Press published ''Hyken's Amaze Every Customer Every Time: 52 Tools for Delivering the Most Amazing Customer Service on the Planet''.<ref>Hyken, Shep. Amaze Every Customer Every Time: 52 Tools for Delivering the Most Amazing Customer Service on the Planet. Greenleaf Publishing Book Group. 2013.</ref>

